FBIS3-43453 "drafr005_c_94018" FBIS-AFR-94-005 Document Type:Daily Report 7 Jan 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA COSATU To Give New Government 5 Years To Reconstruct MB0701071294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network in English 0500 GMT 7 Jan 94 MB0701071294 Johannesburg Radio South Africa Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] COSATU [Congress of South African Trade Unions] has given a new government five years to implement a reconstruction and development program. COSATU says political freedom for workers in 1994 will mean a vote for democracy, a vote for jobs, a vote for peace and a vote for improved living conditions. However, these objectives will be achieved only through a concrete program which sets out clear priorities, targets and time frames.
